Condolences are pouring in for Mandla Hlatshwayo who died when he came to assist victims of a mugging.Minister of Arts and Culture Nathi Mthethwa paid tribute Hlatshwayo saying he is a great loss to the South African entertainment industry.&#8220;It is with a deep sense of shock and sadness that I heard the startling news of the passing of celebrated actor and entertainer, Mandla Hlatshwayo,&#8221; said Mthethwa.Hlatshwayo was shot and killed on Sunday in Soweto, Pimville.The incident happened around 11pm when four armed robbers entered the pub and held people up.&#8220;We appreciate his willingness not only to share his talents with us, but also his efforts to plough back to his community. We also want to see those responsible for taking the life of this young man brought to book,&#8221; said MthethwaMeanwhile the Pan Africanist Congress of Azania (PAC) joins millions of South Africans to mourn the untimely death.Kenneth Mokgatlhe PAC Spokesperson says he was indeed Godsend and for that we appreciate.&#8220;We are saying to his lovely family, our thoughts and prayers are with you. We thank you for having borrowed us your talented and gifted son, brother, father and uncle. He will always be remembered in the entertainment industry by next generations to come,&#8221; said Mokgatlhe.Hlatshwayo was known for his role as Siphiwe Phosa on the SABC1 soapie Generations a role he played for seven years (1999 2006).